## 1. Monorepo Structure

The repo has **two tiers**: a **root full-stack app** and **packages/** (legacy or separate deploy targets).

### Root application (oraicle-retail-promo)

```
oraicle/
├── client/               # Vite 7 + React 19 — SPA
├── server/               # Express, tRPC 11, OAuth
│   ├── _core/            # index.ts (Express + tRPC + Vite), context, trpc, cookies, oauth, vite
│   └── routers/          # agents.ts, catalog.ts
├── shared/               # Shared types and constants (e.g. @shared/const)
├── drizzle/              # MySQL schema (drizzle/schema.ts) + migrations
├── package.json          # Single app: dev (tsx watch server), build (vite + esbuild), test (vitest)
├── vite.config.ts
├── drizzle.config.ts     # dialect: mysql, schema: ./drizzle/schema.ts
└── .env / .env.local     # Root env (see Section 8)
```

- **No pnpm-workspace at root** — root is a standalone app; `packages/` are separate.
- **Story workflow:** `docs/stories/` and `TRACKER.md` may not exist in this workspace; when they do, follow story-driven-development rule.

### Packages (optional / alternate deploy)

```
packages/
├── landing/          # Astro — marketing site + Retail Promo Designer
├── control-panel/    # Next.js — admin + company dashboard (tRPC 11, Drizzle)
├── dashboard/        # Next.js — user dashboard
├── dashboard-2/      # Next.js (alternate, Jest)
├── core/             # Shared lib: Drizzle schema, auth, admin, payment, email
├── auth/             # OpenAuth, JWT, QR codes
├── ai/               # Effect-based AI integration
├── functions/        # SST Cloudflare Workers (Hono)
├── crons/            # Scheduled jobs
└── docs/             # Starlight docs site
```

- **SST:** `sst.config.ts` may be absent; `.sst/` may contain platform/artifacts from another branch or deploy.
- **Migrations:** Root uses `drizzle/` (MySQL); package-level apps may use `migrations/` (e.g. Postgres) when present.

**Package manager:** pnpm at root (no workspace file); packages may use workspace in other setups.
**Drizzle:** Root uses `drizzle-orm` (e.g. ^0.44.x) and **MySQL**; packages may use `@oraicle/core` and **Postgres**.

