## 5. Database & Drizzle

### Root app (MySQL)

- **Schema:** `drizzle/schema.ts` — dialect **mysql** in `drizzle.config.ts`
- **Connection:** `DATABASE_URL` or `DbUrl` (see Section 8)
- **Important tables:** `users` (openId, name, email, role), `suggestionHistory` (RAG, agent, embedding), `suggestionAnalytics`, plus any catalog/sync tables in the same schema
- **Migrations:** `drizzle-kit generate` / `drizzle-kit migrate` (output `./drizzle`)

### Packages (Postgres when present)

- **Schema sources:** `@oraicle/core` — `user`, `payment`, `api`, `admin`, `airdrop`, `price`; control-panel — `enterprise-schema`, `customer`, `email-campaign`, `invoice-numbering`, `products`
- **Connection:** `createDrizzle` from `@oraicle/core/drizzle/index`; control-panel merges tables in `db()`; URL: `Resource.DbUrl.value` (SST) or `process.env.DATABASE_URL`

### Important tables (packages)

- Core: `user`, `payment`, `crypto_request`, `api_token`, `api_token_usage`
- Admin: `admin_users`, `admin_sessions`, `admin_invitations`, `admin_roles`
- Enterprise: `companies`, `company_users`, `documents`, `audit_logs`, `invoices`, `invoice_items`
- Control-panel: `customers`, `customer_segments`, `email_settings`, `email_campaigns`, `products`

