### Root app — Retail Promo / agent (client highlights)

- **`AgentChat.tsx`:** Canvas state, `sendChatMessage` / proactive suggestions, BYOK via `getResolvedLlmApiKey()`, workspace **agent brief**, **design defaults**, **Workspace tools** strip, model mode **fast | smart | custom** with optional `modelPair`. **STORY-189:** **`RETAIL_PROMO_CHAT_STARTERS`**. **STORY-191:** `logRetailPromoEvent('ai_chat_message', { emptyActionsReason })` when the model returns zero actions (privacy-safe enum). **STORY-195:** `agent-chat-engine.ts` appends **`AGENT_SEARCH_ARCHITECTURE_PROMPT`** to the main system prompt so informational answers cite Meilisearch / MiniSearch / LLM rerank without inventing stacks. **STORY-199:** smart LLM skip uses **`shouldSkipSelectProductsLLM`** (`meilisearch-smart-routing.ts`) with `catalog.getSearchProvider` (`hybridEnabled`, `confidenceThreshold`). **STORY-200:** `search-feedback.ts` — `lastAgentCatalogSelectionRef` + `setSelectedProductIndicesFromUser` (implicit deselect) / thumbs → `search_feedback_explicit`.
- **`AdCanvasEditor.tsx`:** WYSIWYG, products, export, workspace Settings tab with section navigation. **STORY-209:** product image → **Change photo** / **Swap product** (catalog row picker aligned with MiniSearch + Products tab “only search matches”).
- **Workspace settings modules (localStorage, browser-local):** `llm-api-key-storage.ts`, `search-settings-storage.ts`, `search-rules-rag-lite-settings.ts` (**STORY-201**), `catalog-api-settings-storage.ts`, `agent-brief-storage.ts`, `design-defaults-storage.ts`, `ionet-model-preferences-storage.ts`.
- **Model lists:** `ionet-models.ts` / io.net API lists available models; **`CHAT_MODEL_PAIR_BY_MODE` / `MODEL_MAP` in `agent-chat-engine.ts`** define chat presets — do not assume they match without checking both. **STORY-192:** `ionet-client` throws **`LlmCallError`** (provider `io.net`, kind `list_models` | `chat_completion`, optional `modelId`, `httpStatus`); use **`formatLlmCallErrorReport`** for UI/logs. Future non–io.net backends should reuse `LlmCallError` with a new `LlmProviderId`.

